type: web_research
title: LINE Bot + AI Chat System Architecture Research 2025-2026
key_insights[11]: LINE Messaging API supports 11 message types including Flex Messages for rich interactive layouts,"SSE (Server-Sent Events) is the optimal streaming approach for AI chat - simpler than WebSocket, auto-reconnect, single HTTP connection","Assistant-UI is the de facto standard for React AI chat interfaces in 2025 (200k+ monthly downloads, Y Combinator backed)","Japanese NLP: MeCab fastest for high-volume, Kuromoji best for Java/Elasticsearch ecosystem, both ~80% accuracy","LINE webhook architecture requires HTTPS TLS 1.2+, signature verification mandatory, no IP whitelisting",Next.js 14+ App Router with Route Handlers preferred over Pages Router for streaming responses,"Flex Messages use CSS Flexbox hierarchy: Container > Bubbles > Blocks/Components","LINE API rate limits enforced with 429 errors, load testing through platform prohibited",SSE implementation requires 'force-dynamic' export in Next.js to prevent Vercel caching,LangChain callbacks enable token-by-token streaming with handleLLMNewToken hook,Japanese intent classification benefits from LLM-based approaches in 2025 (NLP2025 conference findings)
findings[15]: "LINE API supports max 5 messages per reply request, replyToken expires quickly",Webhook signature verification prevents tampering - check X-Line-Signature header,SSL certificate must be from public CA for webhook endpoint,Flex Messages render differently across devices - always test on multiple platforms,Video components in Flex Messages require altContent fallback for older LINE versions,Rich menus support up to 10 LIFF apps per channel for embedded webviews,"SSE format: 'data: {message}\\n\\n' with optional id:, event:, retry: fields",Heartbeat every few seconds recommended to keep SSE connection alive,Redis caching (Upstash) reduces redundant LLM API calls for repeated queries,TextEncoder/TextDecoder required for SSE byte stream handling in browsers,"Assistant-UI handles auto-scrolling, accessibility (WCAG), message state management automatically","Vercel AI SDK provides ready-made Conversation, Prompt, TypingIndicator components",Production chatbots need retry logic with exponential backoff for API failures,Sentinel events in SSE signal connection closure for graceful client handling,LINE Platform logs not provided - developers must maintain own request/response logs
techniques:
  "LINE Webhook Flow": User message → LINE Platform → Webhook URL (HTTPS) → Bot server processes → Reply via LINE API
  "SSE Streaming Pattern": "ReadableStream.start() → controller.enqueue(encoder.encode('data: ...\\n\\n')) → controller.close()"
  "Next.js Streaming Setup": export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'; POST handler returns ReadableStream with text/event-stream headers
  "Client SSE Consumption": fetch() → response.body.pipeThrough(TextDecoderStream()) → getReader() → while loop read chunks
  "LangChain Streaming": "callbacks: [{ handleLLMNewToken(token) { enqueue(token) }, handleLLMEnd() { close() } }]"
  "Flex Message Structure": JSON hierarchy with container (carousel/bubble) → blocks (header/hero/body/footer) → components (box/button/text/image)
  "Signature Verification": "HMAC-SHA256(channel secret, request body) === X-Line-Signature header"
  "Long Message Handling": Split into multiple message objects (max 5 per request) or use push API for additional messages
  "Japanese Tokenization": "MeCab for speed, Kuromoji for Java ecosystem, both with custom dictionary support"
  "Error Recovery SSE": "Implement retry with exponential backoff, send heartbeats, handle browser auto-reconnect"
anti_patterns[15]: DO NOT restrict LINE webhook by IP address - IPs are undisclosed and change,DO NOT use Pages Router for streaming in Next.js 14+ - App Router Route Handlers preferred,DO NOT skip webhook signature verification - opens to spoofing attacks,"DO NOT load test through LINE Platform - violates terms, use mock servers",DO NOT use WebSocket when SSE suffices - unnecessary bidirectional overhead for chat,DO NOT ignore replyToken expiration - send response immediately after webhook,DO NOT hardcode message content for testing on production - may violate user privacy guidelines,DO NOT forget altContent for Flex Message video components - older LINE versions need fallback,DO NOT cache streaming responses in Vercel without 'force-dynamic' - breaks real-time updates,DO NOT assume Flex Messages render identically across devices - always test on iOS/Android,DO NOT send requests to invalid user IDs repeatedly - wastes quota and violates guidelines,DO NOT skip error handling in SSE streams - always implement controller.error() on failures,DO NOT use rule-based Japanese intent classification in 2025 - LLM-based approaches outperform,DO NOT ignore LINE message quota limits - monitor via API to prevent service disruption,DO NOT store sensitive data in LINE webhook logs without encryption - GDPR/privacy compliance
decisions[6]:
  - chose: SSE (Server-Sent Events) for AI response streaming
    over[3]: WebSocket,Long polling,HTTP chunked transfer
    reason: "SSE is simpler (unidirectional sufficient for chat), has automatic browser reconnect, uses single HTTP connection, better suited for LLM streaming than bidirectional WebSocket overhead"
  - chose: Assistant-UI React library
    over[3]: Custom chat UI,Shadcn chat components,Vercel AI Elements
    reason: "Assistant-UI is production battle-tested (200k+ monthly downloads), handles streaming edge cases automatically (auto-scroll, accessibility, state), adopted by LangChain/Stack AI, provides primitives not monolithic components"
  - chose: Next.js App Router Route Handlers
    over[3]: Pages Router API Routes,Express.js,Fastify
    reason: "App Router designed for streaming with Web Request/Response APIs, simpler setup than Pages Router, native Vercel deployment optimization, better TypeScript support"
  - chose: LangChain callbacks for streaming
    over[2]: OpenAI SDK direct streaming,Custom stream parser
    reason: "LangChain provides standardized handleLLMNewToken callback across multiple LLM providers, easier to switch providers, built-in error handling, integrates with Redis caching"
  - chose: MeCab for Japanese tokenization at scale
    over[3]: Kuromoji,Janome,Sudachi
    reason: "MeCab fastest for high-volume processing, custom dictionary support for domain-specific terms, 80% accuracy comparable to alternatives, well-documented for production"
  - chose: Webhook signature verification
    over[2]: IP whitelisting,API key in query params
    reason: "LINE Platform IPs undisclosed and subject to change, signature verification (HMAC-SHA256) prevents spoofing and tampering, recommended in official security guidelines"
refs[10]: "LINE Messaging API Overview: https://developers.line.biz/en/docs/messaging-api/overview/","LINE Development Guidelines: https://developers.line.biz/en/docs/messaging-api/development-guidelines/","LINE Flex Messages: https://developers.line.biz/en/docs/messaging-api/using-flex-messages/","Assistant-UI: https://www.assistant-ui.com/ (200k+ monthly downloads, YC-backed)","SSE Streaming Guide: https://upstash.com/blog/sse-streaming-llm-responses","Next.js Streaming Docs: https://nextjs.org/docs/app/api-reference/functions/next-response","Japanese NLP Comparison: https://elastic.sios.jp/blog/comparison-of-japanese-language-analyzers-performance-verification-of-kuromoji-sudachi-mecab-and-llm/","OpenAI Prompt Engineering: https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/prompt-engineering","Vercel AI SDK: https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/ai-sdk-ui/chatbot","SSE Best Practices: https://www.speakeasy.com/docs/sdks/customize/runtime/server-sent-events"
recommendations[15]: "Use Assistant-UI (@assistant-ui/react) for production React chat interfaces - battle-tested, auto-handles streaming edge cases","Implement SSE over WebSocket for LINE bot AI responses - simpler architecture, better browser support","Next.js 14+ App Router with Route Handlers for API endpoints, not Pages Router",Always verify LINE webhook signatures before processing - prevents spoofing attacks,Cache LLM responses with Redis (Upstash) to reduce API costs and improve response time,"For Japanese NLP: Use LLM-based intent classification instead of traditional rule-based approaches (2025 best practice)","Test Flex Messages on multiple devices (iOS/Android, different LINE versions) before production",Implement exponential backoff retry logic for all LINE API calls (rate limiting 429 errors),Use LIFF (LINE Front-end Framework) for complex forms/interactions requiring webview,Monitor LINE message quotas via API - free tier has monthly limits,"Log all webhook events with timestamps, request IDs, IP addresses for debugging",Use Flex Message Simulator before sending to preview cross-platform rendering,"For streaming: Set Connection: keep-alive, Cache-Control: no-cache, Content-Type: text/event-stream",Handle unsend events appropriately - delete message data when user unsends,"For production: MeCab with custom dictionary for Japanese tokenization at scale"
next[15]: Implement LINE webhook endpoint with signature verification using HMAC-SHA256,Set up Next.js 14 App Router with Route Handler for SSE streaming,Integrate Assistant-UI React components for chat interface,Configure LangChain with OpenAI callbacks for token-by-token streaming,Add Redis caching (Upstash) for LLM response optimization,Implement Japanese intent classification with LLM-based approach,Create Flex Message templates for rich interactive responses,Set up error handling with exponential backoff for LINE API rate limits,"Add comprehensive logging: request IDs, timestamps, webhook IPs",Test Flex Messages across iOS/Android with different LINE versions,Configure LIFF apps for complex user interactions requiring webviews,Monitor LINE message quota via API and implement alerts,Implement unsend event handling to delete message data,"Set up production deployment checklist: HTTPS TLS 1.2+, signature verification, rate limiting",Create development/staging environments with LINE test channels
